When a controller's constructor injected too many interface, the performance will be greatly reduced because of concurrent requests. Each http request causes a new object to be created. Because of the use of dependency injection, many objects that are not used in the current request are also created, resulting in wasted performance. Do you have any idea to optimize performance?

